<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-298-931  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 298 931.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Jan 30 1989 v6 n4 p28(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Gescan acquires GE subsidiary worth $10M. (Gescan International,GE's Gescan Product Department)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gescan International Inc. (acquisitions and mergers)General Electric Co. (divestment).andO;Ticker:    GE.andO;Product:   General Electric GESCAN (Computer) (marketing).andO;Topic:     Information Storage and RetrievalInformation ServicesAcquisitionData Base Management SystemsHardwareTurnkey Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Gescan Acquires GE Subsidiary Worth $10MandM;RESEARCH TRIANGLE PARK, N.C.andP;  -- The assets of the Gescan Product Departmenthave been acquired by the newly formed Gescan International.andM;Gescan is a text search and retrieval system made by Gescan ProductDepartment, a subsidiary of General Electric.andM;GE's decision to sell Gescan Product Department's parent organization, GE'sSemi-conductor Business Division, to Harris Corp. in December precipitatedthis move.andM;&quot;We bought the business from GE, and our investors include GE, Xerox andBoston Capital Ventures, who all hold about equal shares,&quot; said Dale Rowe,president and chief executive officer of Gescan International.andP;  Although theterms of the acquisition were not announced, Rowe said the company is valuedat about $10 million.andM;&quot;The market for next search and retrieval is huge, because everyone is tryingto do things with the information they've filed, but they haven't gotten overthe first hurdles of 'How do I load the information?' and 'How is it easilyretrievable?'&quot; he added.andM;Rowe said that, while other text retrieval systems index words and data,Gescan incorporates a hardware accelerator, which reads entire lists quicklyand performs comparisons between what users are seeking and what's in thetextual database.andM;Gescan comes in two versions, Rowe said.andP;  Gescan plus the hardwareaccelerator is priced between $25,000 and $45,000 depending on the VAX size,number of users and number of parallel processors.andM;A stand-alone second product, Gefile, resembles a &quot;tow-drawer file cabinet,&quot;Rowe said, and includes a MicroVAX, 1GB disk and Gescan.andP;  Gefile supports asmany as 24 simultaneous users and sells for between $70,000 and $100,000.andM;Gescan International is located at P.O. Box 12599, Research Triangle Park, NC27709, (919) 460-3100.andO;</TEXT></DOC>